form.preferredDefinition: The Position Generator is used to gather information about the occupations of relatives, friends, and acquaintances in the person's social network. Acquaintances are people who the respondent knows by face and by name. The occupations, whether prestigious or not, make up the respondent's access to key social resources. The Position Generator used in the 2004 and 2006 U.S. Social Capital Surveys includes questions about 22 jobs and follow-up questions about anyone in the respondent's network who has that job. The interviewer asks the respondent if he/she knows anyone who has that particular occupation. If the respondent answers "yes" the interviewer asks a follow-up question about the relationship between the respondent and this person, how the respondent got to know the person, how long the relationship has existed, how close the relationship has been, and also about the gender and ethnic/racial background of the person.

form.longName: PhenX PX180402 - Disinhibiting Behaviors Impulsivity Child Protocol
form.preferredDefinition: The UPPS-P Impulsive Behavior Scale for Children includes 40 self-administered items that are scored as five subscales (urgency, premeditation, perseverance, sensation seeking, and positive urgency). The respondent is asked to read each item and circle the number on a scale that best describes him/her. The 4-item Likert scale includes values for 1 (not at all like me), 2 (not like me), 3 (somewhat like me), and 4 (very much like me).

headerInstruction.text: Below are a number of statements that describe ways in which people act and think. Read each one carefully and think about whether it is like you. For each statement, please select the statement that describes you.1=not at all like me 2=not l..TRUNCATED

question.questionText: 1. If I feel like doing something, I tend to do it, even if it's bad. (do_what_i_feel_like)
2. I like new, thrilling things to happen. (like_new_thrilling_things)
3. I like to see things through to the end. (pxt180402_see_things_through)
4. I tend to blurt out things without thinking. (blurt_out_things)
5. I am upset when I am not finished with things. (upset_when_not_finished)
6. I like to stop and think about something before I do it. (like_to_stop_and_think)
7. When I feel bad, I often do things I later regret in order to make myself feel better now. (do_things_later_regret)
8. I would like water skiing. (would_like_water_skiing)
9. Once I get going on something I hate to stop. (hate_to_stop_once_going)
10. I like to know just what to do before I start a project. (like_toknow_what_todo)
11. Sometimes when I feel bad, I keep doing something even though it is making me feel worse. (keep_doing_eventhough_makingworse)
12. I enjoy taking risks. (pxt180402_enjoy_taking_risks)
13. It is easy for me to think hard. (easy_to_think_hard)
14. I would like parachute jumping. (would_like_parachute_jumping)
15. I finish what I start. (pxt180402_finish_what_i_start)
16. I try to take a careful approach to things. (take_a_careful_approach)
17. When I am upset I often act without thinking. (when_upset_act_without_thinking)
18. I like new, thrilling things, even if they are a little scary. (like_thrilling_things_even_ifscary)
19. tend to get things done on time. (get_things_done_on_time)
20. When I feel rejected, I often say things that I later regret. (pxt180402_say_things_regret_when_rejected)
21. I would like to learn to fly an airplane. (like_to_learn_to_fly)
22. I am a person who always gets the job done. (always_gets_the_job_done)
23. I am very careful. (very_careful)
24. I almost always finish projects that I start. (pxt180402_almost_always_finish_projects)
25. I like to know what to expect, before doing something new. (like_toknow_what_toexpect)
26. I often make matters worse because I act without thinking when I am upset. (pxt180402_act_without_thinking_when_upset)
27. I would like to ski very fast down a high mountain slope. (ski_fast_down_high_mountain)
28. I tend to stop and think before doing things. (tend_to_stop_and_think)
29. Before making a choice, I tend to think about both the good things and the bad things about the choice. (consider_good_and_bad_things)
30. When I am mad, I sometimes say things that I later regret. (say_things_regret_when_mad)
31. I would enjoy fast driving. (pxt180402_enjoy_fast_driving)
32. Sometimes I do crazy things I later regret. (crazy_thing)
33. When I am very happy, I can't stop myself from going overboard. (cant_stop_going_overboard)
34. When I am really thrilled, I tend not to think about the results of my actions. (dont_think_about_actions_results)
35. When I am in a great mood, I tend to do things that could cause me problems. (pxt180402_do_things_that_cause_problems)
36. I tend to act without thinking when I am very, very happy. (act_without_thinking_when_happy)
37. When I get really happy about something, I tend to do things that can lead to trouble. (actions_lead_to_trouble)
38. When I am really happy, I tend to get out of control. (out_of_control_when_happy)
39. I tend to lose control when I am in a great mood. (lose_control_in_great_mood)
40. When I am very happy, I tend to do things that may cause problems in my life. (when_happy_actions_cause_problems)

Scoring: 1. Lack of premeditation: items 4, 6, 10, 16, 23, 25, 28, 29 (reverse code all but item 4) 2. Negative urgency: items 1, 7, 11, 17, 20, 26, 30, 32 3. Sensation seeking: items 2, 8, 12, 14, 18, 21, 27, 31 4. Lack of perseverance: items 3, 5, 9, 13, 15, 19, 22, 24 (reverse code all items) 5. Positive urgency: items 3340 The reason to reverse code is so that high scores on each scale are in the impulsivity direction. (scoring_180402)

protocol.preferredDefinition: The UPPS-P Impulsive Behavior Scale for Children includes 40 self-administered items that are scored as five subscales (urgency, premeditation, perseverance, sensation seeking, and positive urgency). The respondent is asked to read each item and circle the number on a scale that best describes him/her. The 4-item Likert scale includes values for 1 (not at all like me), 2 (not like me), 3 (somewhat like me), and 4 (very much like me).
